    "explanation": "To keep an object moving with constant velocity, the resultant/net force becomes zero when the forces are balanced. Many forces may act on an object, but if these forces are balanced, then the resultant/net force becomes zero. That is why the object continues to move with constant velocity. Net force is the resultant force; when balanced, it becomes zero. The tendency of a body to resist any change in its state of rest or motion is defined as inertia. [B.P.S.C. TRE-3 July, 2024]",
