    "answer": "A",
    "explanation": "Frictional force acts both in stationary and in moving conditions. The coefficients related to friction are called the coefficient of static friction and the coefficient of kinetic friction. In a stationary condition, there is no displacement; hence no work is done and no energy conversion takes place. But in a moving condition, motion occurs against friction, due to which energy is lost in the form of heat. In other words, kinetic energy is converted into heat energy. [B.P.S.C. Preview]",
    "subject": "Physics"
