    "id": "bpsc-physics-1",
    "topic": "Motion Under Gravity",
    "question": "A truck starts from rest down a hill with a constant acceleration. It achieves 400 meters in 20 seconds. If the weight of the truck is 7 tons then what will be the force acting on it2",
    "options": [
      "11000 N",
      "12000 N",
      "13000 N",
      "14000 N"
    ],
    "answer": "D",
    "explanation": "For motion with uniform acceleration, the equation is: s = ut + 1/2 at². Here, since u = 0, s = 1/2 at². So, 400 = 1/2 × a × (20)² -> 400 = 200a -> a = 400/200 = 2 m/s². Therefore, the acceleration of the truck is: a = 2 m/s². Now, according to Newton's second law of motion: F = ma. Mass = 7 tonnes = 7000 kg. So, F = ma = 7000 × 2 = 14000 N. Thus, the force acting on the truck will be 14000 N. [71 B.P.S.C. (Pre.) 2025]",
