    "explanation": "Swami Vivekananda’s nationalism, which arose during colonial rule and amid the widespread poverty and suffering of the people, was based on Indian spirituality. Swami Vivekananda was a true nationalist from his heart and soul. He adopted a spiritual outlook on nationalism in the struggle for freedom. Subhas Chandra Bose called Swami Vivekananda the “Spiritual father of the modern nationalist movement.\nSource: BPSC (T.R.E.-3) July, 2024",
