    "explanation": "After the failure of the Civil Disobedience Movement, Gandhiji emphasized the constructive programme. In 1934, Gandhiji decided to withdraw from active politics to devote all his time to Harijan uplift. In September 1932, he established the All India Anti-Untouchability League for Harijan welfare, and in 1933 he started publishing a weekly newspaper titled ‘Harijan’.\nSource: 41st B.P.S.C. (Pre) 1996",
