    "explanation": "In the Government of India Act, 1919, a provision was made for appointing an Indian High Commissioner to reduce the workload of the Secretary of State for India. Its functions included purchasing arms and other goods for the Government of India, awarding contracts, looking after commercial interests, and taking care of Indian students studying in England, etc. The expenditure on the salaries of the High Commissioner and his assistants was to be met from India’s resources.\nSource: 63rd B.P.S.C. (Pre.) 2017",
