    "explanation": "In India, during the monsoon season, most cyclones originate between 10° N and 15° N latitude. A cyclone is a low-pressure area in which winds rotate inward. In the Northern Hemisphere, cyclones rotate anticlockwise, and in the Southern Hemisphere, they rotate clockwise.\nSource: B.P.S.C. School Teacher (Class 11th-12th) 15-12-2023",
