    "question": "In Soil, Water that is readily available to plant root is",
    "options": [
      "Humidity water",
      "Bound water",
      "Capillary water",
      "More than one of the above",
      "None of the above"
    ],
    "answer": "C",
    "explanation": "The roots of a tree get water from the soil in the form of capillary water. Capillary water remains stored in the fine pores of the soil. The water that forms the soil solution is loosely held around soil particles. Hence, the water available to plant roots in soil is capillary water.\nSource: B.P.S.C. TRE-3 July, 2024",
    "sourceBook": "BPSC General Studies 2026",
