    "subject": "Indian Geography",
    "section": "Indian Geography",
    "topic": "Transport",
    "question": "Which state had the highest constructed road length under Bháratmala Pariyojana as of 31st October 2024",
    "options": [
      "Rajasthan",
      "Uttar Pradesh",
      "Maharashtra",
      "More than one of the above"
    ],
    "answer": "A",
    "explanation": "Up to 31 October 2024, under the Bharatmala Project, the highest length of constructed roads was in Rajasthan (2,241 km), which was more than Uttar Pradesh (1,854 km) and Maharashtra (1,837 km). By October 2025, a total of 21,351 km of roads had been constructed under the Bharatmala Project. In terms of total constructed length, the top three states were Rajasthan (2,258 km), Uttar Pradesh (2,084 km), and Maharashtra (1,960 km).\nSource: 71st B.P.S.C. (Pre) 2025",
    "sourceBook": "BPSC General Studies 2026",
