    "topic": "Transport",
    "question": "Which of the following two extreme locations are connected by the East-West Corridor",
    "options": [
      "Mumbai and Nagpur",
      "Mumbai and Kolkata",
      "Silchar and Porbandar",
      "More than one of the above",
      "None of the above"
    ],
    "answer": "C",
    "explanation": "The East–West Corridor connects Silchar in Assam with Porbandar in Gujarat. The North–South Corridor connects Srinagar with Kanyakumari. Both corridors were constructed under the National Highways Development Project.\nSource: B.P.S.C. Teacher (9th-10th) 08.12.2023",
    "sourceBook": "BPSC General Studies 2026",
    "sourcePrintedPage": 251,
    "sourcePdfPage": 251,
