    "answer": "D",
    "explanation": "The fourth session of the United Nations Environment Assembly was held in Nairobi (Kenya) from 11 to 15 March 2019. Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the fifth session of the United Nations Environment Assembly (UNEA-5) was held in two parts— First part (UNEA-5.1) – February 2021, Nairobi (Kenya), in virtual format. Second part (UNEA-5.2) – 28 February to 2 March 2022, Nairobi (Kenya). The fifth session of UNEA was held in Nairobi from 28 February to 2 March 2022 in a hybrid mode. The main theme of UNEA-5 was “Strengthening Actions for Nature to Achieve the Sustainable Development Goals.” The seventh session of the United Nations Environment Assembly (UNEA-7) was held from 8 to 12 December 2025 at the headquarters of the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP) in Nairobi, Kenya.\nSource: BPSC) (Pre) 2019",
