    "topic": "Economic Development",
    "question": "a ccording to a rticle 113 of the Constitution, how much Demands for Grants in the annual budget are presented in Parliament",
    "options": [
      "98",
      "96",
      "104",
      "109",
      "None of the above / more than one of the above"
    ],
    "answer": "E",
    "explanation": "According to Article 113 of the Indian Constitution, demands for expenditure (other than expenditure charged upon the Consolidated Fund of India) are presented for the approval of the Lok Sabha. These are called Demands for Grants. No fixed number is prescribed for them. In the current budget, 102 Demands for Grants are included.\nSource: 67th B.P.S.C. (Pre) 2021",
