    "explanation": "Inflation is commonly called rising prices. When, during a period, the prices of goods and services increase and people have to pay a higher price to buy the same quantity of goods and services as before, it is called inflation. In the Indian economy, the following factors can potentially contribute to stagflation—  Decline in industrial production and slowdown in economic growth.  Reduced export competitiveness due to appreciation of the domestic currency.  Decrease in aggregate demand and consumer spending.  High inflationary pressure due to an increase in government spending, etc.\nSource: 69th B.P.S.C. (Pre) 2023",
