    "explanation": "National Food Security Mission (NFSM; started from the 2007–08 Rabi season) is a Centrally Sponsored Scheme. It was launched with the target (up to 2011–12, i.e., till the end of the 11th Five-Year Plan) of achieving additional production of wheat, rice and pulses by 10, 8 and 2 million tonnes respectively (total 20 million tonnes additional foodgrains). Up to the end of the 12th Plan, the target was 25 million tonnes additional foodgrains production—10 million tonnes rice, 8 million tonnes wheat, 4 million tonnes pulses and 3 million tonnes coarse cereals. Based on past experience and performance, the programme period was extended up to 2019–20, with an additional foodgrains production target of 13 million tonnes (rice 5 million tonnes, wheat 3 million tonnes, pulses 3 million tonnes and coarse cereals 2 million tonnes). At present, oilseeds and oil palm have also been included under NFSM. However, as per the question period, option (a) was the intended answer.\nSource: 56th to 59th B.P.S.C. (Pre) 2014",
